<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRESIDENT BUSH'S DECISION TO ALLOW LOGGING IN OWL COUNTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The effort to save the spotted owl from extinction may cost thousands of lumber 
industry workers their jobs. It all comes down to which is more important: the 
welfare of human beings or animals? Owls are usually associated with wisdom, 
but the campaign to preserve them at the expense of humans is one dumb 
decision. 
</P>
<P>
KENNETH L. ZIMMERMAN 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 
</P>
</TEXT>
