<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOTTERY WINNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
How much have you won on the California Lotto this year? 
</P>
<P>
My wife, Helen, is now ahead exactly $520, and that's only since the first week 
of January. After years of trying, the most she ever won was a fiver (dollars, 
that is) and that was last December. 
</P>
<P>
So, instead of going to the local 7-Eleven, she started putting her 
$10-twice-a-week "investments" into a glass jar. 
</P>
<P>
That's how she got $520 ahead, last count. 
</P>
<P>
Pretty soon, now, she's planning on taking that grubstake to Las Vegas where 
she's bound to be better entertained and, possibly, even win a little. 
</P>
<P>
JACK B. KENNETT 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
