<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: RADIO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cruise Races to Radio: Tom Cruise has gone from the racetrack to the radio to 
hype his "Days of Thunder" film, which is doing less-than-zooming business at 
the box office. 
</P>
<P>
Cruise visited KIIS-AM (1150) and KIIS-FM (102.7) morning personality Rick Dees 
for an hour Thursday in what was apparently his only local radio interview. The 
actor told Dees that he liked Maria McKee, Melissa Etheridge, the Rolling 
Stones, AC/DC and Technotronic's "Pump Up the Volume." Cruise also said he 
considers "Days of Thunder" a huge hit already. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
