<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG BRAXTON, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Like a Rolling Stone: Rolling Stones bassist Bill Wyman will record his first 
solo album in nine years when the Stones wind up their current world tour. The 
album is planned for release in March. Fellow Stones Mick Jagger, Keith 
Richards and Charlie Watts have all had outside projects in recent years that 
were met with no more than moderate popularity. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
