<HEADLINE>
<P>
6 HURT AS AMTRAK TRAIN, TRACTOR-TRAILER RIG COLLIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MERIDIAN, Miss. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Amtrak train collided with a tractor-trailer rig Thursday, injuring six 
people, authorities said. Four of the injured were reported in good condition 
at Jeff Anderson Regional Hospital; the others were treated at Riley Memorial 
Hospital, hospital officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
