VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: PORT HUENEME; 
</P>
<P>
CORONER REPORTS MAN WAS STRANGLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Port Hueneme man who was found dead in his seaside condominium died of 
strangulation, but authorities could not locate the businessman's family to 
notify them of his death, the Ventura County coroner's office said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Bruce Eugene Pope, 62, was a self-employed, free-lance business consultant, 
whose severely beaten body was found Wednesday in a condominium in the 900 
block of Lighthouse Way, Investigator Jim Wingate said. 
</P>
<P>
"We've exhausted our resources finding relatives," Wingate said, explaining why 
Pope's name was released before his relatives were notified. 
</P>
<P>
Port Hueneme police will not release the method of strangulation and are not 
certain what objects were used in the beating, Wingate said. 
</P>
<P>
This is the second homicide in Port Hueneme since 1988, said a spokeswoman for 
Port Hueneme Police Chief Bob Anderson. It is at least the ninth slaying in 
Ventura County since January. KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
