<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was a bad day all the way around for accused bank robber Alexander Hatfield, 
27, of Scripps Ranch Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Bill Robinson said Hatfield was the suspect who Thursday 
morning robbed the HomeFed Bank branch in the 10000 block of Scripps Ranch 
Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
It was hardly a high-scoring heist. After demanding that a teller hand over 
money, the robber fled with $331. 
</P>
<P>
Then, the robber had trouble getting his car out of the bank parking lot, 
giving bank employees time to get his license number and relay it to police. 
</P>
<P>
A short time later, Hatfield found himself being pursued by police. The pursuit 
ended when he crashed his car into a tractor-trailer at Mercury Street and 
Engineer Road in Kearny Mesa, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Police arrested Hatfield and found $331 dollars in his pocket, according to 
Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
Hatfield was in jail Thursday night, and the FBI said it would bring a 
bank-robbery charge against him and would check to see if he is a suspect in 
any other bank robberies. 
</P>
