<TEXT>
<P>
A 16-year-old girl was slightly wounded by a stray bullet while watching a 
fireworks display with her family in National City Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
Ena Anderson, 16, of Paradise Hills was hit in the head by the bullet, Police 
Officer David Grande police said. 
</P>
<P>
"She felt something hit the left side of her head. (The bullet) appeared to 
have been falling free after being shot in the air," Grande said. A doctor at 
Paradise Valley Hospital removed a .22-caliber bullet from under the skin. 
</P>
<P>
The Morse High School senior's mother, Vernell Anderson, said her daughter 
received five stitches. "She's got a whopping headache, but she's smiling 
through it," she said. 
