<TEXT>
<P>
Spelling Entertainment Idles Sale Plans: Spelling Entertainment, which 
announced Sept. 29 that it was exploring a sale to help reduce parent Great 
American Communications Co.'s debt load, said it did not find satisfactory any 
of the recent bids submitted to buy the company. 
</P>
<P>
Spelling is 46% owned by GACC, which in turn is controlled by Cincinnati 
investor Carl M. Lindner. GACC had put Spelling up for sale in order to pay off 
$125 million in reset notes due in October, but that debt is now being 
restructured. A senior Spelling executive did not rule out an eventual sale of 
the company if a buyer makes an attractive bid. 
</P>
</TEXT>
