<P>
Western Digital Sued for Patent Infringement: Cadtrak Corp., a small computer 
graphics licenser in San Mateo, Calif., said it filed a lawsuit against Western 
Digital and one of its subsidiaries for allegedly infringing two Cadtrak 
patents that cover several fundamental functions in most computer graphics 
devices. Cadtrak's suit, filed in U.S. District Court in San Francisco, did not 
specify damages. Western Digital said in a statement that Cadtrak's claim lacks 
merit and that it will file a countersuit asking for treble damages against 
Cadtrak. 
