<HEADLINE>
<P>
EASTERN EUROPE FILMS IN GAY &amp; LESBIAN FEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
More than 100 films from 15 nations will screen during the Los Angeles 
International Gay &amp; Lesbian Film and Video Festival today through July 12 
at the Directors Guild of America, 7920 Sunset Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
Four films about gay men and women in Eastern Europe are included: 
</P>
<P>
* East Germany's "Coming Out," Friday at 7:30 and 9:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
* "Another Way," a feature-length film from Hungary, about two women 
journalists during the 1956 uprising, Saturday at 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
* "Sex 121 and the Gulag," about the spread of AIDS in the Soviet Union, and 
"Polskiseks," a documentary about Poland's Solidarity movement and the Catholic 
Church working together to ban abortion, Monday at 7 p.m. Both short films are 
from Britain. 
</P>
<P>
Festival information: 650-5140 
</P>
</TEXT>
