<HEADLINE>
<P>
'DIE HARD 2' BLAZES ON THE 4TH OF JULY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JACK MATHEWS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Die Hard 2," 20th Century Fox's entry in the summer '90 Box Office Blockbuster 
Sweepstakes, grossed $5.9 million on July 4, a day that is traditionally low in 
attendance because of the outdoor celebrations associated with the holiday. 
</P>
<P>
"It's Christmas," shouted a jubilant Tom Sherak, president of marketing and 
distribution at Fox. 
</P>
<P>
"If you'd told me we would do just under $6 million on July 4, I would have 
told you to go to the hospital for a mental checkup." 
</P>
<P>
Sherak said the studio would have been happy with a $4-million July 4; as it 
turned out, "Die Hard 2" grossed almost that much from its preview opening 
Tuesday. The $3.7-million Tuesday receipts will not be counted as opening-week 
figures, however. 
</P>
<P>
"Tuesday is Tuesday, a preview day," said Sherak, preparing some tangled logic. 
"We opened on Wednesday and Tuesday's figure have nothing to do with the 
opening." 
</P>
<P>
The Fox executive declined to predict how well the film will do through Sunday, 
but other analysts said it could do as much as $30 million, which would make it 
the strongest-opening film of the year. 
</P>
<P>
July 4 figures were not released by other studios. JACK MATHEWS 
</P>
</TEXT>
