<TEXT>
<P>
Washington Capital defenseman Scott Stevens has signed an offer sheet with the 
St. Louis Blues worth $3 million over three years, the St. Louis Post-Dispatch 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
The offer would make Stevens, 26, the NHL's highest-paid defenseman. 
</P>
<P>
The Capitals have seven days to match the figure and retain Stevens, who has 
429 points and 1,628 penalty minutes in 601 games over eight NHL seasons. He 
became a free agent July 1. 
