<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BRIEF BLAZE AT SCHOOL FORCES STAFF 
EVACUATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire in the ventilation system at a South-Central Los Angeles elementary 
school Thursday forced at least nine of the school's administrative staff to be 
evacuated. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured in the fire that broke out on the roof of the school office 
building at 68th Street Elementary School, but there was extensive smoke 
damage, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Damage estimates were not immediately available. Classes at the year-round 
school were to begin again today. 
</P>
