<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FREEWAY SHOOTING VICTIM IN CRITICAL 
CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorist who was shot in the head as he drove onto a Ventura Freeway on-ramp 
in Sherman Oaks was in critical condition Thursday at the Medical Center of 
North Hollywood, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was identified as Juan Manrique, 18, of Arleta. He was shot about 
9:30 p.m. Wednesday as he turned from Woodman Avenue onto the westbound 
entrance to the freeway, Lt. Warren Knowles said. The gunman fired five or six 
shots at Manrique and a 20-year-old passenger from a passing car on Woodman, 
Knowles said. The passenger was not hit. 
</P>
<P>
The motive for the shooting was not known, and police said they had no 
indication that it was gang-related. 
</P>
