<P>
FIGHTING COCKS, HENS FOUND; MAN CITED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM MCQUEENEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 50-year-old Cypress man was cited Thursday for possession of fighting cocks 
after a police officer discovered about 40 individually caged roosters which 
had been altered for combat, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Also discovered in the man's front and rear yards in the 8300 block of Denni 
Street were about 20 breeding hens and 100 chicks, Lt. John Schaefer said. 
</P>
<P>
Demosthenes Ariosa was issued a misdemeanor citation and ordered to appear in 
Municipal Court in Westminster on Aug. 15. 
</P>
<P>
Police were called to the Ariosa residence at about 1:15 p.m. after a neighbor 
complained that Ariosa had been shooting at a dog that was bothering his 
chickens. No charges were brought in that matter, Schaefer said. 
</P>
<P>
Orange County Animal Control officers seized some of the roosters to be used as 
evidence against Ariosa, he said. TOM MCQUEENEY 
</P>
