<HEADLINE>
<P>
DREIZLER LEAVES UCI FOR UCLA BASEBALL JOB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Robin Dreizler, an assistant baseball coach at UC Irvine, has resigned to 
become an assistant at UCLA, Irvine Coach Mike Gerakos said. 
</P>
<P>
Dreizler, who has worked under Gerakos at Irvine the past seven seasons, will 
work with the pitchers at UCLA, as he did at Irvine. He replaces Tip LeFebvre, 
who resigned. 
</P>
<P>
John Altobelli, who has been an assistant at Irvine for three seasons, will 
become Gerakos' full-time assistant, and a pitching coach will be hired, 
Gerakos said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
