<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSMAKERS: DYNACHEM ELECTRONIC PROMOTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Daniel D. Feinberg has been appointed executive vice president of Dynachem 
Electronic Materials, a Tustin-based unit of the Specialty Chemicals Group of 
Morton International Inc. 
</P>
<P>
He will be responsible for U.S. operations, including marketing and sales, 
manufacturing, research and development and logistics. 
</P>
<P>
Feinberg, who joined the company in 1971, had previously been senior vice 
president, marketing and sales. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, S.J. Haywood was promoted from vice president to senior vice 
president of European operations, and Hideji Muramatsu, formerly general 
manager of Japanese operations, was named vice president of Dynachem-Japan. 
</P>
<P>
Dynachem supplies specialty chemicals and equipment to the printed circuit and 
semiconductor industries. 
</P>
