<P>
POLICE SHOOT IRVINE TAXI-THEFT SUSPECT AFTER FREEWAY CHASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man driving a taxicab stolen in Irvine shot at pursuing police along the 
crowded San Diego Freeway this morning before he was cornered and shot by 
officers in Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified suspect was shot an unknown number of times by at least one 
uniformed officer as he hid in a gully near the intersection of Moulton Parkway 
and Laguna Hills Drive. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect was taken to a nearby hospital for treatment of his gunshot wounds, 
Irvine police Lt. Vic Thies said. His condition was unknown. 
</P>
<P>
The man allegedly stole the taxi at a hotel and drove onto the freeway. He was 
spotted at Irvine Center Drive by police, who began a high-speed pursuit. 
</P>
<P>
As the suspect approached El Toro Road, he began firing a .45-caliber automatic 
handgun at the officers, blowing out the rear window of the yellow taxi, police 
said. The suspect continued to fire shots, leaving the freeway at Oso Parkway 
and driving through several Laguna Hills neighborhoods. 
</P>
<P>
The gunman left the cab when he blew out a tire after driving over a concrete 
median strip. 
</P>
<P>
The incident began at 9:50 a.m. when the man approached taxi driver Valery 
Yakubov, 29, of Anaheim, at the Holiday Inn in Irvine, Thies said. He allegedly 
robbed and beat Yakubov, then drove off in his cab. 
</P>
</TEXT>
