<TEXT>
<P>
Marla Maples' mother and aunt are suing the National Enquirer, saying the 
supermarket tabloid published unauthorized photographs of the model who was 
romantically linked with businessman Donald Trump. 
</P>
<P>
The lawsuit, filed Thursday in U.S. District Court, seeks unspecified damages 
from the Lantana, Fla., paper. 
</P>
<P>
Maples' mother, Ann Ogletree, of Dalton, and aunt, Pat Locklear, of Cohutta, 
allege that the Enquirer published without their permission photographs taken 
by the two women. 
</P>
<P>
The pictures show Trump with Maples and various members of her family. They 
were published May 1 under the headline, "Caught! Trump and His Mistress. World 
Exclusive Amazing Photos That Could Cost him illions." 
</P>
<P>
The Enquirer has also been sued by Maples' father, who said in an unrelated 
suit that the newspaper falsely claimed to have interviewed him. 
