<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
YALE CREW SURVIVES SHAKY START 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HENLEY-ON-THAMES, England 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Yale University overcame problems with a soft-spoken umpire and an abrupt start 
to reach the quarterfinals of the Thames Cup at the Henley Regatta today. 
</P>
<P>
Yale won a thrilling race by three-quarters of a length against an English crew 
from Lea Rowing Club, but only after recovering from the confusing starting 
procedure of the 151-year-old regatta. 
</P>
<P>
Yale's bowman was still checking his oarlock when the start was called, and he 
missed his first stroke. The rest of the crew, feeling that something was 
amiss, began tentatively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
