<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
24 HURT IN SOUTH AFRICA BLAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, South Africa 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A powerful bomb blew up today next to a downtown bus terminal used mainly by 
blacks, injuring at least 24 people. 
</P>
<P>
Police blamed right-wing extremists. 
</P>
<P>
The blast on a busy street during the morning rush hour sent concrete and 
debris hurtling through the air, a police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
"There were rocks flying into the air. There was blood everywhere, people 
screaming and crying," said Nhlanhla Mbatha, who was waiting in line for a bus 
when the bomb went off. "It was only black people who got injured." 
</P>
<P>
Doctors said most of the 24 injuries were not grave. The independent South 
African Press Assn. said two people were hospitalized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
